Summary:
This week’s podcast breaks down the challenges Amazon Prime Air drones face and what Apple might want to do with a massive Twitter firehouse. Plus, a little advice for new media folks still trying to figure out their business model.
Half-hour delivery service from Amazon sounds great, but do you mind a drone landing at your front door? That’s what Amazon envisions and on this week’s podcast we discover the implications and obstacles of this brave new world. New media and “old” Twitter is also in the spotlight, so we break it all down and try to figure out which media models will work and what Apple plans to do with a Twitter firehose.
